data.title: Unit-4 Henry Fielding: Joseph Andrews: B.A. (Hons.)
data.meta_description: Unit-4 - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. This document provides information about Henry Fielding's novel Joseph Andrews, including biographical details about Fielding. It discusses how Fielding was influenced by Don Quixote in writing Joseph Andrews. Fielding had a difficult childhood and youth. The document outlines key events in Fielding's life and career, including his struggles with money and debts. It notes similarities between Don Quixote and Parson Adams from Joseph Andrews. The document also provides a summary of the plot of Joseph Andrews and analyzes themes and characters in the novel.
